<p>Due to Aurora's temperature extremes, dual-fuel systems combining electric heat pumps with gas furnace backup provide excellent efficiency and reliability. These systems use the heat pump during milder weather and automatically switch to gas heating when outdoor temperatures drop below the heat pump's effective range. For the city's 1,920 square foot average home size, properly sized systems typically range from 2.5 to 4-ton capacity, depending on insulation levels, window efficiency, and home orientation. Smart thermostats with zoning capabilities can further optimize energy usage, especially important when paired with solar panel systems to maximize self-consumption of generated electricity.</p>

